< review>
This is the first negative review I have ever written.

The used fridge we purchased arrived with a broken thermostat. We've had warm food for a week, which is fine, a risk we took buying a used fridge.

A repair tech came to look at the fridge (no charge per 30 warranty, awesome!) Unfortunately he entered our home without a mask. When asked very kindly, even apologetically, to put one on tech responded that he never wears a mask, and doesn't have one to put on.

I called the company to ask if they were aware they were sending unmasked techs into peoples homes. I spoke with Chris on the phone who said yes, they were aware. Yikes!

It feels extra hypocritical because they have a "Covid-19 Policy" of only dropping off the used fridge OUTSIDE of the house for the safety of employees. Call me cynical, but it would seem that this company has used Covid-19 as an excuse to save time and labor when convenient for them, but doesn't actually care about the health of staff and customers.

So, again, if you are into unmasked strangers entering your home, this is a great company to work with. If you care about personal/public health, not so much.</review>

As a new rider I was pretty nervous and hesitant while shopping for a bike. I was really put at ease by the entire staff at Honda of Glendale, and especially by Brian, who was incredibly patient, friendly, informative and helpful while I came back multiple times, asked a thousand questions, hemmed and hawed, and was not sure what I wanted for a long time. Brian gave me zero pressure, zero "upsell", only excellent, patient advice -- and a GREAT price on a new bike, with much less dealer fees than any other places I was looking at. When I finally purchased a bike, I didn't feel safe riding it home through rush-hour traffic -- so Brian agreed he would deliver it to my home on his flatbed the next morning for an incredibly reasonable fee. Everything about my experience here was excellent. Brian also gave me several very welcome riding tips (lane position, etc) that I still think about every time I take a ride.< /text>

<Response>None< /Response><review>BEST SERVICE IN THE SAN GABRIEL VALLEY!!!
Brian is the best.  He listens, and his his explanations are thorough and easy to understand.  Brian knows everything there is to know about Honda Motorcycles.  A 5 minute talk with Brian completely restored my faith in Honda Motorcycle.  My first was a 1989 Hurricane in 1994.

My 2014 Honda CB500X was losing oil, and the color looked off, at just under 5000mi.  Temple City Powersports, where I purchased the bike, had no explanation for the symptoms and were happy to charge me $98 to check for leaks. If they did not find any, I would owe $98 for them to tell me what I already knew; it's not leaking.

Brian explained why I was losing oil and that the color was nothing to worry about.  It's only 500cc, and riding it at 6-7k rpm on the freeway, at 75-80mph will cause some oil loss.  I happily paid $70 for an oil change, because I knew it was in good hands.

Bert's Mega Mall tried to charge me for a Valve Clearance Adjustment at the first 600mi service.  Over $200 more than the proper service should cost.  They did not check to see that the Maintenance Schedule has changed, but I would have paid for their oversight.

Honda of Glendale has good prices for their new bikes.  You can't go wrong here, if you own a Honda motorcycle.< /review><user_name>K. Moore< /user_name>< gmapID>

<Name>Jason Fracaro<//Name><time>1513361549470<//time><rate>4<//rate><review>TL;DR

‚Ä¢ Prices were honest.
‚Ä¢ Work was done quickly and efficiently.
‚Ä¢ Vibe and a welcoming atmosphere improved over past visits
‚Ä¢ I will be back again

**Update**
December 2017
It was the first time meeting Brian today, who was pleasant to deal with over the phone yesterday and had an appointment wide open for me today.

Dropped off the CBR for an oil & filter change plus brake flush. To my surprise Brian had me in and out in just over an hour. So kudos on that, considering most shops don't have that kind of turnaround. Of course it all depends on the workload of the shop, and so I consider myself lucky today.

The vibe and experience today was a night and day difference in comparison to the other times I have stopped in at the parts department. Luis was in good spirits and Lamon was a hoot. I suppose it's all in the company you keep which can lend a difference to the atmosphere one makes for its customers.

Additionally, I was able to take a walk around the showroom floor and chat it up with Brian. Lowdown is he's one of the owners and the shop has been family owned since the early 80's; it's always good to be able to support local businesses.

Upon pickup we discussed some adjustments and minor tweaks to get more performance out of the motorcycle and better longevity out of the motor.

Prices were reasonable for the work and time put in on the motorcycle; it didn't cost me an arm or a leg. And Brian did make a suggestion for going with a higher performance brake fluid, but was not pushy about it which I appreciated on both fronts; both for the performance recommendation and for not being pushy about it ‚Äî subtly is key.

All in all, I think I will be back. And I would like to be a repeat customer as long as the consistency in service is there and I feel like I am met with honest work along with a second family and home for my bikes.

I am not sure where the shop sits with the riding community, but I could see a future wherein the shop plays host to a club or host their own events & rides to increase visibility and engagement within the motorcycle community ‚Äî especially amongst Honda riders. That would be amazing.

===

July/August 2017
I've never been a fan of their parts department. Customer service is just not their thing.

I never felt welcomed at the location when dealing with the parts department in person or on the phone. I have always felt like I'm inconveniencing them or that they have better things to do with their time than to deal with customers.

How does this inspired confidence in me, especially when I need some service done or better yet, when I am in the market to purchase a new motorcycle? It doesn't.<//review><pictures>None< /pictures>< Response>
None<//Response>

< Text>
La Donut is by far the best donut shop in Anaheim and most of the O.C. Every time my family and I buy a dozen from La Donut we are amazed at their consistency. They're always fresh and delicious. No exaggeration. We've tried all of the classics and have never been disappointed. Their price is usually less than $9. You just can't beat them. <user_name>Stephanie V<//user_name>< review>
A nice family owned donut shop. The earlier you come in, the more variety you will find.

Location: The location itself is within a small plaza off of Anaheim Blvd. Parking is a bit limited, but not too much of a problem.

The Food: The Donuts here are really good. They also have bagels, ice cream, ham and cheese sandwiches, coffee, hot chocolate, and anything you love from a classic donut shop. Their cake donuts are amazing. My personal favorite is a pink donut they have with white icing, delicious! The owners always give free donuts with any donut purchase. A dozen is about $6 and a large hot chocolate is around $2.25, which is huge.

The most important thing to remember when visiting this donut shop is that they do not take credit cards, ONLY cash!

Overall good donuts, the owners are sweet, and good selection.<//review>

<userid>105667530784122452864< /userid>< username>
Rex Anderson< /username>
<time>1461052244598< /time><rate>5< /rate>< Text>
I, too, am very picky about Orange Chicken. One of the best things about Thai Fantasy is that if you have a particular way you would like your choices prepared, the chefs will do their best to meet your expectations. I REALLY DO NOT LIKE the typical orange chicken on most Asian or Fusion restaurant menus in the vast Los Angeles area. Most of what I've experienced is doughy mush balls like what you might get at a Panda Express, for example, or any of the countless strip mall buffet / fast food, barely Chinese places that exist in abundance around here. I like my orange chicken extra crispy and Thai Fantasy has yet to disappoint me. If I order vegetables in brown sauce, and I like their brown sauce even if it is a bit salty, I request that my order have very little sauce. I don't like to waste food, so I make it as clear as possible exactly what I'd enjoy and on only a very few occasions when I was "experimenting," did I get a menu item that was unsatisfying. I for one am not a fan of fish heads. They make me paranoid, like they're staring at me with that one cataract clouded eye! I say if you give a place like Thai Fantasy a fair chance, have more than one meal there before giving them a bad review. The staff, servers, and food prep chefs will extend every courtesy to make sure that everything about your meal meets your expectations. They have done so for me 99 times out of 100... and that one bad experience I had... I believe I was so drunk, unlike how I am normally, that I ordered something so far out that my digestive tract was unprepared. That night I, like others who have left reviews here, worshiped at the feet of the porcelain Buddha! I didn't blame the food, I blamed the booze and my stupidity. As for the folks who got bad meat or ill prepared food, I hope they realize that restaurants that have been in business as long as Thai Fantasy do not, and cannot put up with such customer dissatisfaction. Don't you think they'd be out of business in a heartbeat if their food was always so very  bad and the service always sucked? Here's an idea, if you get something bad, that you don't like, or that might taste odd, or  that smells like poop: SEND IT BACK AND GET SOMETHING ELSE! Seriously, did someone really struggle with bad meat, finding 80% of it terrible? That means they continued to sample it even though it was awful. Why? This is America where no one who can afford it should ever be dissatisfied with a meal anywhere! In conclusion,  I really like this place. I'm just sad that so many seem to have had a bad experience while eating at Thai Fantasy. I'm not crying, but I could be...<//Text>

I hope they pick up their game because I really love this place it's a part of Chula Vista history.<//Review>

<Pictures>None< /Pictures>< text>
I order from here regularly but tonight was the first time there was an issue with my order. Not only was my problem handled with literally zero trouble, they had the replacement pizza at my house in less than 15 minutes, and sent me an extra pizza! The food is excellent, and though I haven't been to the restaurant itself in a long time, I do have tons of fond memories about eating there after soccer games as a kid.

La Bellas Pizza has been in business in Chula Vista longer than I've been alive and it's clear to see why. They're a local business who takes care of their customers and their food is great. What more could you ask for?< /text>

< text>
I love La Bella in Chula Vista. I am a long time native of this city and this place has been a memory of mine with family and friends since I was a young child. Its family orientated but also has a bar and is a laid back casual setting for ALL ages. The food is super delicious. The bread is so good and the employees are friendly and very courteous. The place gets packed on the nights mostly on weekends but there is always parking because people come and go quite regularly here. You can park in the back and enter behind or go up the ramp to the face paced more kid friendly dining area. I love the fettuccini Alfredo. Super damn good you can add chicken or shrimp but the sauce is mouthwatering. My good friend TOMMY works here as he has for more than 10 years. He is good friends with the owner. I highly recommend this place for any occasion or just take out or have it delivered. You won't be disappointed!!! God bless you and be kind to others please...you never know what exactly a person is going through and nobody is qualified to criticize or judge any other person as they themselves are not perfect.üíõüíôüíúüíö‚ù§< /text>

<userid>100528237348693578287<//userid>< review>
I been dining here off and on for a long time, since the late 1960s. The food has always been good, especially the pizza. I prefer a medium Papa's favorite, as it seems to be cooked perfectly every time. The large is very good, but once in a while is not cooked quite as perfectly as the medium size. Pastrami sandwich, and lasagna are other favorites. Antipasto salad great, too. Prices are good. One of my all-time favorite places.</review>

When we arrived to pick up our order it wasn't ready yet. They apologized and let us know that the online ordering isn't always trustworthy. They got us the pizza as fast as they could. < Text>
A true community favorite. I don't remember a time when it wasn't there. Its not enough to say that it's a 3rd Avenue staple, but rather it's turned into 3rd Avenue's foundation.
The reason is simple, the food. Yes the owners and workers are nice and hospitable, and yes there's something for everyone a simple sit down restaurant, a full bar, arcade for the kids and place for special events. All of this is great, but without the freshly, handmade pizza and amazing cheesey bread and astounding pasta none of it would be worth it.

Try it for yourself, you'll see why we locals love La Bella's and why we would never want it to leave.
P.s. I always get the out of this world lasagna! Highly recommend it!üëåüèª‚ú®</Text>

<text>The pizza there doesn't look like much when you get it but once you bite in,  it is amazing how many toppings they cram in each bite.  I took my whole crew out to lunch. About 18 guys 1 gal and they are all hard working large shipyard workers with mean appetites. Only 5 pizzas and a few pitchers of soda and every one was stuffed and left satisfied. The pizza was cut into thin little slivers but each slice was loaded with toppings.  I ordered a 6th meat lovers pizza and no one had any room in their bellies and ended up taking it home with me.  Took me all weekend to finish it.  I invited the crew to lunch thinking it was gonna cost me 3 or 4 hundred bucks to feed them... It ended up being closer to $150. Everything was delicious, service was amazing, and everyone left very satisfied.< /text>< pics>

< Text>
I've been coming here for more than 20 years and the food never disappoints. Before I sit down I always order the garlic cheese bread as it's always made fresh and is delicious. They now have a games side which is great for the kids and parties. Pool tables,  NFL TVs, and a bar for the grown ups makes it a great atmosphere. Definitely a local favorite and hidden gem</Text>

< review>
La Bella's is one of those places that gives me a familial, small-town feel in the Southbay. I've come here in the past for a school banquet, family birthdays, and a graduation celebration. This time around, it was for a going away dinner. We showed up on a Friday evening needing a table for 12, no reservation,and checked in on the 3rd ave side of the restaurant. The lady said there was a 1 hr wait, but had us check with the newer side with the games. Luckily we did, they were able to seat us right away. They have vegetarian friendly options, I got the eggplant parmesan. It was cheesy and good!! The Texas toast that came with it was yummy too. They could work on getting better tasting tap water, and making the long tables not too close to each other, it was hard to get in and out.

Other than that, they have pool tables, arcade games with tickets for prizes, a medium sized banquet room to rent for events, a bar, and TVs for sports. Staff was super friendly on both sides.<//review>

<rate>5</rate>< Review>
La Bella Pizza is a fun and delicious place for yummy Italian food. It's a staple in Chula Vista and has been for years.  All the natives know about La Bellas.  It's old and the hype is real.  My favorite dish is the Papa's Favorite Calzone! Oh my goodness, so fantastic.  Their prices are so affordable for such great quality of food. Their pizzas are to die for and the antipasto salad is so good too.  If you want to have an event you can reserve the top floor.  I went to a bridal shower there. Or you want a fun spot to watch the game on the tube or play games, they have an adjacent building where they expanded the pizzeria. It's a must visit for Chula crowds.</Review>

<text>Utterly and completely disappointing.

Went here because we had heard the pizza was awesome. Okay, we'll give it a shot.

We walk in and the lady who took us back to the dining room said "you're server will be with you eventually, we're busy." Hard to believe considering there were maybe only one or two other tables filled.

Server did show up shortly thereafter which was nice. We ordered a pizza to share.

For anyone who has been underway on a Navy vessel, you know the kind of pizza you get on the line for  "pizza and wing" night or if you have to stay out for a weekend because port ops can't support securing you to the pier. Yea....this pizza was eerily similar to that stuff. Flavorless crust and toppings (something I didn't know was a possibility).

Had to eventually go ask the bartender for a refill on our drinks because our server disappeared after delivering the pizza.

Maybe this place is worth a visit if you're coming for a beer and to watch a football game. Absolutely not worth coming for the food.< /text><pictures>None</pictures></record>

<Text>La Bella's is the premier family run pizza restaurant in Chula Vista.  It's been there since the 50s and even expanded in recent years to open include an & games wing of the restaurant.  Their pizza is the winner as the cheese it really good and the crust is more like a party than bread.  They have a lot of other Italian dishes to choose from as well lots of different torpedo sandwiches.  It's a great place to take the family or just pick up a pizza to go.  They also deliver to a limited area as well so as long as you live close enough they'll bring it to your house.  Anything on the menu is fair game and you can place orders online at their website too.<//Text>< Resp>

Jay Onrails<//username>
< time>
1547743976533<//time>
<Rate>3<//Rate>< Text>
This is my third visit to Bella. I won't mention the previous two just yesterdays dilemma. What's worse than going out to a meal and it not having it go the way you would like? Recommending the place to family and spouting off how great it is and then having it not go the way expected. First off (how I dislike to use that term) the food has been, is and probably will be great for a long time. The waitstaff however is another story altogether. We ate in the first dining room. We were greeted right away and were asked for our drink orders. It was obvious that our young server was new to employment and to the service industry. We were a table of four. We all ordered sandwiches. Forty-three minutes later the first sandwich came. Five minutes later the second sandwich came. When asked what the problem might be the server immediately stated it was the 'boys in the kitchen'. I had full view of the kitchen's service window. There were a lot of stares our way and I was actually a little embarrassed for the server. My guesstimate was that the server just forgot to turn the order in and she was frazzled because of it. For minutes later our third sandwich was delivered. Five more minutes later my sandwich finally arrived. I applaud the 'boys' in the kitchen for banging out the food as quick as possible. The food was incredible. Unfortunately in the restaurant business there are two factors in my opinion, service and quality of food. Bella, you're wonderful. Server(s), make note of how the well seasoned servers at Bella handle their tables. Good luck...Thank you, Jay<//Text>

We had a awesome time !!! I booked my grandson's birthday party here in the game room side and it went great.  The people that had the party before us went a little over their time slot but they got everything cleaned up very very fast and and worked with us because that made us run a little behind as well. <Rating>4< /Rating>< Text>
Great place for some pizza, beers, and some pool table fun. You can bring the kids to the arcade section and be worry free. The food is good but the selection is basically pizza or wings. The only drawback is that if you dont make a reservation you will be stuck waiting, even if you do you cant be there for long because they will force you to move if there is another party waiting. Parking is also scarce so I would recommend getting there early or youll be forced to pay for parking in the surrounding streets. Great place for an afterwork beer if you can find parking and a spot at the tables.</Text>

<userid>108240251362248498654</userid><name>Esmeralda Ramirez</name>< Date>
1414305852447</Date>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
I used to come here all the time during my community college days and order the lasagna with a long island iced tea. Those were definitely the days. Now I have to worry about cholesterol and sugar content. Pfft. Anyway, the back area is catered more toward families and larger groups and it has plenty of arcade games for the kids. They also sell gelato in the back game area.

In general, beer and other adult friendly drinks are cheap here and most of their menu is comfort food. My favorites include their lasagna, pizza, and cheesy bread! Ask for a side of Frank's Red Hot to dip the cheesy bread, it's amazing.<//Text>

<userid>118314736893778948737</userid><user_name>jasonhelio29< /user_name><time>1537514124115<//time><rating>5<//rating>< text>
Great place. The Original seating area is cozy. Darcy is a great waitress that always says hello to me even if I'm not seated in her area. There's a bar with tv to watch games.
The new Area can be a little loud (at busy times) but its a great large area, able to seat lots of large 8-10 peeps tables. Tv's for games. Pool tables & arcade games. My son loves playing after eating, allows us adults to relax & chat so we domt have to leave right away.
Pizza is Very very good. Lasagna is good. Family makes cannolis fresh. The Wings, yes the wings are very tasty. Many choices of Wing sauce, we usually get them on the side.
Great Staff also. Food is served pretty timely.< /text>

<Review>The management was completely unprofessional and disrespectful. I will never book a party at La Bella‚Äôs again.

I made a reservation for 3 tables at 2:00 pm in the new game center side of La Bella‚Äôs for Saturday November 22, 2014 for my daughters end of season soccer party. I arrived a little early at approx. 1:30 in which I was told my reservation was not until 2:30 however 2 tables were available and I was able to prep the cake table and setup our trophies. I asked the manager (James) when the third table would be ready as there was a party occupying the table and he said it would be available by 2:30. I was not exactly pleased with my party having to wait 30 minutes for our table but let it go as our entire party had not arrived yet. As it got closer to 2:30 I again asked our assigned waitress as to when the party was expected to depart in which she said they only had the tables until 2:30 and ensured me my reservation was for 3 tables.

Once the party left and the table was cleaned and set my party occupied the table. About 15 minutes later the Manager James came and informed me that I did not make reservations for 3 tables but 2 and we needed to move. I argued that I in fact made reservations for 3 tables and knew for a fact that we were expecting 35-40 people (each table seated only 15) and needed at least 3 tables. He said we HAD to move. He was very unapologetic and when I said I would give a bad review for this online he shrugged his shoulders and rolled his eyes and said he didn‚Äôt care (great for business!). He then made our party move from the table. We had to eat in shifts so everyone had a chance to sit down to enjoy their food.

The party that was seated at our third reserved table also complained to the same Manager (James) because they had made a reservation for more people than the 15 seat table could seat in which James responded ‚Äúcan‚Äôt the parents go sit somewhere else.‚Äù REALLY! They informed us that they made reservations for room in the back of the restaurant which another party was in. They kicked us out of our reserved table because they made a mistake!

We were offered no apologies by management whatsoever for the inconvenience. I apologized to the waitress and let her know I knew it was not her fault when she responded ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt worry this happens every Saturday.‚Äù Well at least they are consistent! I am team mom for my daughters team and will never bring our team parties to this establishment nor will I ever recommend this establishment to any other teams.< /Review>< user_name>

<text>The management was completely unprofessional and disrespectful. I will never book a party at La Bella‚Äôs again.

I made a reservation for 3 tables at 2:00 pm in the new game center side of La Bella‚Äôs for Saturday November 22, 2014 for my daughters end of season soccer party. < Text>
After waiting for an hour and a half for a table that we were told would take no longer than 40 min, my girlfriend and three young children were placed into a booth where not even the waiters knew what was going on. We had our first waiter who took our drink order then left. right after him we had another waiter come by and ask for our drink order. with her we placed our appitizer order. we then had to flag her down later to place our food order. while waiting for our meal a child pulled the fire alarm and the staff as a whole had no idea what to do. if there had been a real fire we would have all probably died because the staff sat around joking and laughing while the alarm was going off. it was aroung this time that we saw our original waiter bussing tables, that would explain the wait for the table and our food that we could see in the kitchen are. once our food arrived it was less that subpar and gave us all stomach aches the next day. when i approached to manager about it he had an excuse for everything and compted my drinks and appitizer very unhappy with this place now. if i go to drink and play games maybe but i'd rather go somewhere else.</Text>
